<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/University-of-Nottingham-The-Duke-of-Portland-Developing-Solutions-Scholarship" title="University of Nottingham – 'The Duke of Portland Developing Solutions Scholarship'" alt="link">University of Nottingham – 'The Duke of Portland Developing Solutions Scholarship'</a></h2>

	
					<p>
A Full Tuition Fee Scholarship is available for a student from Africa for the MSc in Crop Improvement at the School of Biosciences. You can apply for this scholarship if you
- are a national of (or permanently domiciled in) Africa and
- are classed as an overseas student for fee purposes and
- already hold an offer to start a full-time Masters degree programme for the MSc in Crop Improvement at Nottingham in 2011.The closing date for applications is 6th April 2011. </p>
							<p><span class="date">21/01/2011</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
