						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/2011-Call-for-Proposals-START-Grant-Awards-for-Global-Environmental-Change-Research-in-Africa" title="2011 Call for Proposals START Grant Awards for Global Environmental Change Research in Africa" alt="link">2011 Call for Proposals START Grant Awards for Global Environmental Change Research in Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>START, the global change ‘SysTem for Analysis, Research and Training’, a programme formed in 1992 under the aegis of the International Council for Science (ICSU, Paris, France) has launched the Call for Proposals (CFP) for the ‘2011 START Grant Awards for Global Environmental Change Research in Africa’. The Grant Awards will be offered to African scientists to support collaborative research with other African scientists and/or with scientists in other areas of the world. Application materials and instructions for submission of proposals can be found at the <a href="http://start.org/programs/africangec/2011-call-for-proposals-start-grants-gec-research-africa" target="_blank">START website</a>. Proposals are due on 06 December 2010. (Source: Start.org; 2 November 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">17/11/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/2011-Call-for-Proposals-START-Grant-Awards-for-Global-Environmental-Change-Research-in-Africa">Read more...</a>
